## Logical Summary

Tritestium rests on a simple rule:

> Ecological truth is recognised only when independent witnesses converge.

Each witness class contributes a distinct form of knowledge:

| Witness | Contribution |
|--------|--------------|
| Human | contextual interpretation |
| Observational | continuous environmental observation |
| Laboratory | biochemical verification |

None alone is sufficient.

Together they form a **distributed ground-truth protocol for ecological systems**.

